AB  - The Coastal Observation and Seabird Survey Team (COASST) is a 20 year-old, data-driven marine citizen science program monitoring ∼450 sites from northern California to Utqiagvik, Alaska and west through the Aleutians. COASST collects data on beachcast birds, and marine debris. An active participant corps of 800 monthly data collectors makes the program one of the larger marine science-public partnerships in the world. The program was started to create a baseline of beach deposition against which untoward change could be measured. Critical to program success is integration of the scientific and academic communities as collaborators, grant co-principal investigators, and advisory board members. A comprehensive participant support strategy including personalized feedback, active listening for co-creation and co-production opportunities, translation of COASST science in ways that are relevant and meaningful to coastal communities, and elevation of participants as skillful knowledge holders, has allowed the program to recruit broadly and enjoy high retention rates. © 2022 Elsevier Inc. All rights reserved.
